{
  "texts": [
    "The relativistic critic evaluates the policy's answer and the expert's answer in a pairwise fashion rather than in isolation.",
    "Without this relativistic setup, the reward signal perceived by the policy exhibits significantly higher variance during training, as illustrated in Figure 13.",
    "This instability suggests that the reference answer serves as a crucial anchor enabling stable optimization.",
    "We further demonstrate that the critic successfully learns to utilize the tie option defined in our relativistic setup.",
    "As shown in Figure 12, the critic learns to output tie stably for around 70% of the outputs after around 150 training steps."
  ]
}